-- French Business Confidence Rises in July; Consumer Confidence Unchanged
-- Jeffrey Donovan
-- 2010-07-22T06:45:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/french-business-confidence-rises-in-july-consumer-confidence-unchanged.html

          
          
             French busines confidence rose in
July while consumer confidence was unchanged, national
statistics institute Insee said today in an e-mailed statement.  
 The index of sentiment among factory executives increased
to 98 from a revised 96 in June, Insee said. Economists expected
a reading of 94, the median of 15 forecasts gathered by
Bloomberg News showed.  
 A gauge of household sentiment was unchanged at minus 39,
Insee also said. Economists expected a reading of minus 40,
according to the median of 13 forecasts gathered by Bloomberg
News.  
          
          


  


        